PROBLEM: 'What is the value of '\[3+\frac{1}{3+\frac{1}{3+\frac13}}?\]'\n'$\textbf{(A)}\ \frac{31}{10}\qquad\textbf{(B)}\ \frac{49}{15}\qquad\textbf{(C)}\ \frac{33}{10}\qquad\textbf{(D)}\ \frac{109}{33}\qquad\textbf{(E)}\ \frac{15}{4}$'\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \ \frac{31}{10}
[B]: \ \frac{49}{15}
[C]: \ \frac{33}{10}
[D]: \ \frac{109}{33}
[E]: \ \frac{15}{4}

PROBLEM: 'The infinite product\n'\[\sqrt[3]{10} \cdot \sqrt[3]{\sqrt[3]{10}} \cdot \sqrt[3]{\sqrt[3]{\sqrt[3]{10}}} \ldots\]'\nevaluates to a real number. What is that number?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \sqrt{10}
[B]: \sqrt[3]{100}
[C]: \sqrt[4]{1000}
[D]: 10
[E]: 10\sqrt[3]{10}

PROBLEM: 'What is the value of '\[(\log 5)^{3}+(\log 20)^{3}+(\log 8)(\log 0.25)\]' where '$\log$' denotes the base-ten logarithm?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: ~\frac{3}{2}
[B]: ~\frac{7}{4}
[C]: ~2
[D]: ~\frac{9}{4}
[E]: ~3

PROBLEM: 'The roots of the polynomial '$10x^3 - 39x^2 + 29x - 6$' are the height, length, and width of a rectangular box (right rectangular prism). A new rectangular box is formed by lengthening each edge of the original box by '$2$'\nunits. What is the volume of the new box?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \frac{24}{5}
[B]: \frac{42}{5}
[C]: \frac{81}{5}
[D]: 30
[E]: 48

PROBLEM: 'Isosceles trapezoid '$ABCD$' has parallel sides '$\overline{AD}$' and '$\overline{BC},$' with '$BC < AD$' and '$AB = CD.$' There is a point '$P$' in the plane such that '$PA=1, PB=2, PC=3,$' and '$PD=4.$' What is '$\tfrac{BC}{AD}?$'\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: \frac{1}{4}
[B]: \frac{1}{3}
[C]: \frac{1}{2}
[D]: \frac{2}{3}
[E]: \frac{3}{4}

PROBLEM: 'A circle with integer radius '$r$' is centered at '$(r, r)$'. Distinct line segments of length '$c_i$' connect points '$(0, a_i)$' to '$(b_i, 0)$' for '$1 \le i \le 14$' and are tangent to the circle, where '$a_i$', '$b_i$', and '$c_i$' are all positive integers and '$c_1 \le c_2 \le \cdots \le c_{14}$'. What is the ratio '$\frac{c_{14}}{c_1}$' for the least possible value of '$r$'?\n'
=======
CHOICES:
[A]: ~\frac{21}{5}
[B]: ~\frac{85}{13}
[C]: ~7
[D]: ~\frac{39}{5}
[E]: ~17
